From: R9700 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-11
Subject: [PATCH] sampler: extend --enable-nan-detection to catch +/-Inf

`Sampler._preprocess_logits` checks `isnan(logits)` but not `isinf(logits)`.
On ROCm, `softmax(+Inf)` produces NaN (because exp(+Inf)/sum(+Inf, finite)
is NaN/NaN), then `torch.multinomial` on NaN returns an invalid index,
then `torch.gather` faults with `HSAIL 0x1016` async — the same crash
surface as raw NaN logits but caused by upstream Inf instead.

This patch adds an `isinf` branch parallel to the `isnan` branch in
`_preprocess_logits`.  Behavior matches the NaN branch:
- log a warning identifying which sample had bad values
- replace +Inf with `+1e4`, -Inf with `-1e4` (same magnitude as the
  NaN→`-1e5` replacement, but signed-aware)
- escalate to `ValueError` when `crash_on_warnings()` (i.e. when
  `SGLANG_IS_IN_CI=1`) so test runs fail loudly

Required to make the gemma4 26B HSAIL bisect repeatable: without this,
the Inf logits would propagate to NaN and the existing NaN check would
catch them only AFTER an already-corrupted softmax — losing the signal
about whether the model produced Inf-finite or NaN to begin with.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/sampler.py
@@ -78,6 +78,18 @@ class Sampler(nn.Module):
             if crash_on_warnings():
                 raise ValueError("Detected errors during sampling! NaN in the logits.")

+        # Catch +/-Inf logits — softmax(+Inf) → NaN cascade, then multinomial
+        # returns an invalid index, then torch.gather faults (HSAIL 0x1016 on
+        # ROCm). Same severity as NaN; --enable-nan-detection covers both now.
+        if self.use_nan_detection and torch.any(torch.isinf(logits)):
+            logger.warning("Detected errors during sampling! Inf in the logits.")
+            logits = torch.where(
+                torch.isinf(logits) & (logits > 0), torch.full_like(logits, 1e4),
+                torch.where(torch.isinf(logits), torch.full_like(logits, -1e4), logits),
+            )
+            if crash_on_warnings():
+                raise ValueError("Detected errors during sampling! Inf in the logits.")
+
         return logits

     def forward(
